<dl id="n01025a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01025a">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01025a"> 25(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> intermit / preter &mdash;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If a debtor acknowledges only sixpence when he owes a pound, he should be allowed to pay that sixpence; but let us not for a moment <mark>intermit</mark> the demand, that the remaining balance be paid up before the otherwise inevitable hour of bankruptcy arrives. <small> J. S. Mill, <a name="JSME" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JSME"><cite title="source">England and Ireland</cite></a>, (1869) 42</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05108e" href="c05all.htm#c05108e">VI.C.05:108(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
